article.headline: Navy 73, Radford 71
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, MD. -- Kaleo Kina scored a career-high 30 points to lift Navy to a 73-71 overtime victory over Radford on Saturday night. Navy trailed by one point until Kina made a pair of free throws, giving the Midshipmen (5-1) a 69-68 lead with 1:07 remaining in overtime. Kina then nailed a long 3-pointer to put the Midshipmen ahead by four points. Guard Amir Johnson responded with a 3-pointer to pull Radford within one point at 72-71 with 13.6 seconds to left in the game. But Kina made two free throws to help Navy pull away. Reserves Clif Colbert and Romeo Garcia scored eight points each for the Midshipmen. Johnson scored 19 points for Radford (2-3), which led by as much as seven in the first half and held a 31-27 lead at halftime. Martell McDuffy had 14 points and Kenny Thomas added 12 for the Highlanders.
